<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Area">
    <statement>
        <p> A semicircle is positioned with the curve opening up (like a smile) and a rectangle is attached cleanly to the top of the semicircle. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: the semicircle has radius 9 and the rectangle has height 11, where everything is measured in meters.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total area of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>A \approx 325.23</m> <m>m^2</m>. This was computed using the formula <m>A = \frac{1}{2}\pi r^2 + b h</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
